Create a Bar Chart with the Number of Supermarkets per Brand¶

In [30]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x=df_count.index, y=df_count.values, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Number of Supermarkets per Brand')
plt.xlabel('Brand')
plt.ylabel('Number of Supermarkets')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

Create a Scatterplot Matrix for Numeric Variables¶

In [31]:
numeric_cols = ['lat', 'lon', 'pop', 'pop_dens', 'frg_pct', 'emp']

g = sns.PairGrid(df[numeric_cols])

g.map_lower(sns.scatterplot)

g.map_diag(sns.histplot)

g.map_upper(sns.scatterplot)

plt.show()

Plot the Locations of Supermarkets by Brand¶

In [32]:
df = pd.read_csv('supermarkets_data_enriched.csv')[['id', 'brand', 'lat', 'lon']]

df_sub = df.loc[df['brand'].isin(['Coop', 'Migros', 'Denner'])]

colors = {'Coop': 'green', 'Migros':'orange', 'Denner': 'red'}

plt.scatter(df_sub['lon'], df_sub['lat'], c=df_sub['brand'].map(colors))
